review:
Pros:
- Great pixel graphics;
- 3 elements to play with;
- Responsive controls;
- Some mission variety;
- Replayability (New game+ and option to turn on advance enemy AI);
- Most of soundtrack is great;
- Good upgrade system;
- Enemy variety;
- Co-op;

Cons:
- 4/5 of levels is overly liniar;
- Some bugs;
- Lack of manual saves;
------------------------------------------
++..++

Decent 2d stealth platformer with cool art style and fun elemental system set in classic fantasy setting. Overall, it is an enjoyable experience and it is fun to mess around with different elements, but main shortcoming that limits game potential is bad level design. If you not expect hardcore stealth fun, check it out.

Pros:
- Great pixel graphics;
- 3 elements to play with;
- Responsive controls;
- Some mission variety;
- Replayability (New game+ and option to turn on advance enemy AI);
- Most of soundtrack is great;
- Good upgrade system;
- Enemy variety;
- Co-op;

Cons:
- 4/5 of levels is overly liniar;
- Some bugs;
- Lack of manual saves;
